
Here's the source code of the lux kernel, a simple Unix-like kernel aiming to
provide compatibility with existing Unix applications.

The source code is organized in several directories in a simple manner.

	acpi/			ACPI and APIC implementations.
	asm_i386/		i386-specific code in assembly.
	asm_x86_64/		x86_64-specific code in assembly.
	firmware/		Firmware device drivers, PIT, HPET, etc.
	io/			I/O device drivers, keyboard, tty, etc.
	mm/			Memory management.
	misc/			Things that don't fit into any other category.


